<paragraph blockId="4.[113,753,733,949]" pageId="4" pageNumber="326">
Bartsch described numerous subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kobelt" authorityYear="1902" box="[615,752,733,757]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pupinidae" genus="Schistoloma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Architaenioglossa" pageId="4" pageNumber="326" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[615,752,733,757]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="326">Schistoloma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the 
<collectingCountry box="[219,344,765,789]" name="Philippines" pageId="4" pageNumber="326">Philippines</collectingCountry>
, differing from one another only by shell colouration and shell size. Bartsch is widely known to be as an extreme splitter (see review in 
<bibRefCitation author="Watters GT" box="[585,740,829,853]" pageId="4" pageNumber="326" refId="ref4653" refString="Watters GT (2006) The Caribbean Land Snail Family Annulariidae: A Revision of the Higher Taxa and a Catalogue of the Species. Backhuys, Leiden, 584 pp." type="book" year="2006">Watters, 2006</bibRefCitation>
), and in the present case his subspecies do not seem to be worth maintaining. In the list below we recognise only species-level taxa.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
